This paper focuses on information extraction from text, which is a common topic in natural language processing (NLP) and computational linguistics (CL). Therefore, cs.CL is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses machine learning techniques, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (AI) research (cs.AI). The paper deals with knowledge base curation, which is related to databases (cs.DB). The paper also deals with query answering, which is related to information retrieval (IR) (cs.IR). Finally, the paper deals with statistical techniques for dealing with sparse and skewed observations, which is related to machine learning (cs.LG).
